
Installing Miniconda and creating environments:
-----------------------------------------------

Download conda from  https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html

sh Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh #install (answer no when asked: Do you wish the installer to initialize Miniconda3 by running conda init? [yes|no])

eval "$(/home/namd5/vini_3_1/miniconda3/bin/conda shell.bash hook)" #activate base conda env

conda create -n Vini python=2.7        #create conda env Vini with python 2.7

conda activate Vini                    #activate conda env Vini

conda install pandas mpi4py requests   #install programs in conda env Vini

Install custom packages #optional¸
--------------------------
conda install -c conda-forge cookiecutter



Managing conda environments:
-----------------------------

Activate conda's base environment in the current shell session without modifying ./bashrc:
eval "$(/home/namd5/vini_3_1/miniconda3/bin/conda shell.bash hook)" #activate base env without modifying .bash

conda info --envs                    #list conda environments

conda activate  Vini                 #activate conda environment Vini

conda deactivate                     #deactivate active environment

conda env remove -n ENV_NAME         #remove conda environment

